						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up before the Sakalēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1074, Uttarāyaṇa Saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 55 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Sakalēśvara by Jāmenāyaka. The gift was entrusted to Malānabōya for supply of ghee to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
